vec::Vec::<T, A>::clear.doc:
Clears the vector, removing all values.

Note that this method has no effect on the allocated capacity
of the vector.

# Examples

```
let mut v = vec![1, 2, 3];

v.clear();

assert!(v.is_empty());
```

