doc:
Truncates this `String`, removing all contents.

While this means the `String` will have a length of zero, it does not
touch its capacity.

# Examples

```
let mut s = String::from("foo");

s.clear();

assert!(s.is_empty());
assert_eq!(0, s.len());
assert_eq!(3, s.capacity());
```
